Source: gitfs
Maintainer: PressLabs <ping@presslabs.com>
Section: python
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7.4.3), python (>= 2.7), python-dev, python3-dev,
    python-setuptools (>= 2.2), python-pex-cli | python-pex, fuse, libgit2-dev, libffi-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.3

Package: gitfs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, fuse, libgit2, python-dev
Description: Mount git repositories as local folders
 gitfs is a FUSE file system that fully integrates with git. You can mount a
 remote repository's branch locally, and any subsequent changes made to the
 files will be automatically committed to the remote.
